Package: multifer
Title: Typed Perturbation Inference for Projector-Based Multivariate Models
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Bradley",
           family = "Buchsbaum",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "brad.buchsbaum@gmail.com")
Description: One platform with two engine families: a latent-root
    family and a predictive-gain family. The package is not a fitting
    framework: you fit your model with multivarious (or any compatible
    package that provides the required accessors via a thin adapter)
    and multifer provides the inference layer on top -- the collapsed
    Vitale P3 ladder, sequential-deflation significance, rank-matched
    bootstrap, and variable / score / subspace stability summaries.
    The mature tier covers PCA-family one-block variance inference,
    covariance-mode two-block methods (PLSC-family), and shipped CCA
    paths on the supported paired and nuisance-adjusted designs. The
    present tier adds generalized-eigen inference via LDA and
    predictive-gain inference via PLSR; multiblock remains planned.
    Built around typed shapes (geometry, relation, design), strict
    dispatch, machine-enforced validity contracts, latent-unit output
    schemas, and a clean separation between permutation-based
    significance and bootstrap-based stability.
